CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 3, 1951, pg. 22 reads: "Food From The Gods - At the completion of installation formalities of Alpha Omicron Lambea Chapter of Alpha Phi Alpha recently, this hungry group of brothers and their guests partook of a sumptuous repast prepared by the famous caterer, Roberta Bailey Lewis, of Frozen Foods fame. in left foreground are Atty. A. D. Stevenson and Dr. Charles Crampton, two of the pioneer Pittsburgh Alphas. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alpha Phi Alpha members, including A.D. Stevenson, back right, Dr. Charles Crampton, Wilbur Douglass, reaching for food between Dr. Charles Cephas and Charles H. Cuthbert; Alexander Allen, back right, and George Mason, right; and guests holding appetizers in hands, standing around table of food in Alpha Phi Alpha house during installation ceremonies, 3046 Centre Avenue
